Here are both approaches for .NET MAUI Shell navigation with `IQueryAttributable`:

**1. Passing a simple string ID**

```csharp
// ProductListPage.xaml.cs or ViewModel command
async void OnProductSelected(Product product)
{
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"ProductDetailsPage?productId={product.Id}");
}
```

**2. Passing the full object via a dictionary**

```csharp
async void OnProductSelected(Product product)
{
    var navParams = new Dictionary<string, object>
    {
        { "product", product }
    };
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("ProductDetailsPage", navParams);
}
```

**Receiving both on the ViewModel with `IQueryAttributable`:**

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId { get => _productId; set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value); }
    public Product Product { get => _product; set => SetProperty(ref _product, value); }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach 1: simple string parameter
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service, etc.
        }

        // Approach 2: full object (passed via dictionary overload)
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product product)
        {
            Product = product;
            ProductId = product.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

**Wire up the ViewModel as `BindingContext`:**

```csharp
// ProductDetailsPage.xaml.cs
public ProductDetailsPage(ProductDetailsViewModel vm)
{
    InitializeComponent();
    BindingContext = vm;
}
```

**Register the route and DI:**

```csharp
// MauiProgram.cs or AppShell
Routing.RegisterRoute("ProductDetailsPage", typeof(ProductDetailsPage));

// In DI
builder.Services.AddTransient<ProductDetailsPage>();
builder.Services.AddTransient<ProductDetailsViewModel>();
```

**Key differences:**

| | String param | Object param |
|---|---|---|
| **Method** | Query string in URI | `Dictionary<string, object>` overload |
| **Received as** | `object` (string at runtime) | Original typed object |
| **Survives deep link / URL** | ✅ Yes | ❌ No (requires in-app navigation) |
| **Use when** | Simple IDs, bookmarkable routes | Avoiding redundant DB lookups |

Shell calls `ApplyQueryAttributes` on the page's `BindingContext` automatically if it implements `IQueryAttributable` — no extra wiring needed beyond setting the `BindingContext`.
